        <a name="systemRequirements"></a>
        <h2>System requirements</h2>

        <ul>
		 <li>Esri Maps for Dynamics CRM requires an account that is part of an <a href="http://help.arcgis.com/en/arcgisonline/help/#/What_is_ArcGIS_Online/010q00000074000000/">ArcGIS Online</a> organization and access to Microsoft Dynamics CRM, either online or on-premises. See <a href="http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/hh699710.aspx">Microsoft Dynamics CRM web application requirements</a> for operating system and software requirements.</li>
		 <li>Esri Maps for Dynamics CRM supports the following browsers: Internet Explorer 9, Internet Explorer 10*, Chrome (latest), Firefox (latest), and Safari (Mac OS X 10.7 and 10.8).</li> 
		 <li>•	Esri Maps for Dynamics CRM supports the following environments: Dynamics 2013 (on Premise), Dynamics 2015 (on Premise and Online). The latest version of Esri Maps for Dynamics CRM does not support CRM 2011. Please contact <a href="http://support.esri.com/phoneSupport#us" title="Esri Customer Support">Esri Support</A> if you require support of Dynamics CRM 2011.</li>
		</ul>
		
		<p>*Internet Explorer 10 compatibility is limited to the desktop browser and does not extend to the touch-based version.</p>

        <a name="whatsNew"></a>
        <h2>What's new</h2>
        <p>Esri Maps for Dynamics CRM version 1.0.2 was released in April 2015. This version includes the following improvements:</p>
        <ul>
			<li>Support for Microsoft Dynamics CRM 2015</li>
			<li>Support for Enterprise Logins</li>
			<li>Bug fixes</li>
        </ul>
		
